1
00:01:08,068 --> 00:01:10,195
<i>The war is over.</i>

2
00:01:12,406 --> 00:01:14,365
<i>The terms of peace</i>

3
00:01:14,366 --> 00:01:19,580
<i>forced Finland to cede
territory to the Soviet Union.</i>

4
00:01:21,582 --> 00:01:25,126
<i>Four hundred and
twenty thousand Finns</i>

5
00:01:25,127 --> 00:01:27,170
<i>had to leave their homes</i>

6
00:01:27,171 --> 00:01:31,091
<i>and move to the Finnish
side of the new border.</i>

7
00:01:33,927 --> 00:01:39,308
<i>The majority of the forcibly
displaced were from Karelia.</i>

8
00:01:40,851 --> 00:01:45,856
<i>Most of them would
never see home again.</i>

9
00:07:43,213 --> 00:07:45,090
Yeagor Dragunov.

10
00:07:51,263 --> 00:07:55,142
Several missions
behind the enemy lines.

11
00:07:56,768 --> 00:07:59,687
Your team burned
down entire villages.

12
00:07:59,688 --> 00:08:02,190
Killed hundreds of civilians,

13
00:08:02,191 --> 00:08:05,360
including a two-year-old boy, Otso,

14
00:08:06,069 --> 00:08:10,157
a six-year-old boy, Otava,
and their mother, Tuulikki.

15
00:08:12,951 --> 00:08:17,122
"We chopped them into
little pieces with a shovel."

16
00:08:17,915 --> 00:08:19,833
We were saving bullets.

17
00:08:20,959 --> 00:08:23,754
That was the family
of Aatami Korpi,

18
00:08:24,505 --> 00:08:27,089
a Finnish commando,
who took revenge

19
00:08:27,090 --> 00:08:30,469
by killing over 300
soldiers of the Red Army

20
00:08:31,428 --> 00:08:32,930
and became a legend.

21
00:08:34,473 --> 00:08:35,516
Koschei...

22
00:08:36,641 --> 00:08:37,809
the immortal.

23
00:08:39,269 --> 00:08:42,939
This killing machine entered
Soviet Union ten hours ago.

24
00:08:45,025 --> 00:08:47,569
I'm sending you to
clean up your mess.

25
00:08:49,238 --> 00:08:51,197
Destroy the legend you created,

26
00:08:51,198 --> 00:08:54,159
and you will go back
home a rich man.

27
00:13:30,853 --> 00:13:32,646
Passport, Mr. Dragunov.

28
00:13:55,627 --> 00:13:58,338
I think the legend
has been homesick.

29
00:13:59,464 --> 00:14:03,719
That is all that is left
from his life before.

30
00:14:04,678 --> 00:14:05,679
Go on.

31
00:15:43,944 --> 00:15:44,945
Go on!

32
00:17:29,174 --> 00:17:31,133
Keep your eyes open.

33
00:17:31,134 --> 00:17:34,346
This one is a crafty
old motherfucker.

34
00:18:08,797 --> 00:18:09,798
No.

35
00:18:40,037 --> 00:18:41,663
Keep very still.

36
00:19:49,565 --> 00:19:52,359
I fucking told you to keep still.

37
00:26:24,877 --> 00:26:25,878
Unleash hell.

38
00:41:37,289 --> 00:41:38,290
Talk to me!

39
00:41:39,875 --> 00:41:41,376
We found the truck!

40
00:41:42,252 --> 00:41:44,004
Did you find the body?

41
00:41:49,259 --> 00:41:50,385
What about the cargo?

42
00:42:00,062 --> 00:42:02,064
You stubborn motherfucker.

43
00:42:03,815 --> 00:42:07,110
Still heading home
to Finland, aren't you?

44
00:44:44,852 --> 00:44:46,770
Took you fucking long enough.

45
00:46:30,624 --> 00:46:31,959
Hold your position.

46
00:49:20,210 --> 00:49:21,503
We want him alive.

47
00:50:05,422 --> 00:50:07,382
There's no place like home.

48
00:51:17,369 --> 00:51:18,537
Get out.

49
00:52:05,876 --> 00:52:09,670
I have killed so many
women and children

50
00:52:09,671 --> 00:52:14,760
that I cannot remember
any particular person.

51
00:52:16,929 --> 00:52:21,141
I remember shouting, crying.

52
00:52:22,392 --> 00:52:27,564
I remember the begging.
But I cannot recall any faces.

53
00:52:30,442 --> 00:52:31,568
Except for one.

54
00:52:34,947 --> 00:52:37,950
It's stuck in my mind,

55
00:52:38,659 --> 00:52:40,244
like it was important.

56
00:52:42,621 --> 00:52:43,747
A small boy.

57
00:52:45,499 --> 00:52:48,126
Tried so hard to be
the man of the family.

58
00:52:48,710 --> 00:52:54,466
I remember him because he
produced a knife out of thin air.

59
00:52:55,133 --> 00:52:56,927
Almost took my eye.

60
00:53:03,851 --> 00:53:05,185
Otava.

61
00:53:10,482 --> 00:53:12,150
Tough little fucker.

62
00:53:13,235 --> 00:53:15,279
Make any father proud.

63
00:53:16,905 --> 00:53:22,452
He tried hard to protect his
little brother, and his mother.

64
00:53:26,707 --> 00:53:31,503
We chopped them all into
small pieces with an iron shovel.

65
00:53:32,963 --> 00:53:38,051
It was a feast for the... the
homeless, the stray dogs.

66
00:53:41,763 --> 00:53:44,850
They're saying I lit
a fire in you. All right.

67
00:53:45,684 --> 00:53:46,935
I will put it out.

68
00:53:48,312 --> 00:53:51,230
You are a mistake, an aberration.

69
00:53:51,231 --> 00:53:54,902
You are a... a
byproduct of my work.

70
00:53:56,028 --> 00:53:58,363
A fucking weed in my field.

71
00:53:59,114 --> 00:54:00,616
And where you are going...

72
00:54:02,409 --> 00:54:04,243
they will beat the
legend out of you

73
00:54:04,244 --> 00:54:06,204
till there is nothing left of you.

74
00:54:06,205 --> 00:54:08,749
Not even a memory.

75
00:54:09,374 --> 00:54:11,418
And your home...

76
00:54:15,547 --> 00:54:19,551
the logs of your house
will be railroad ties,

77
00:54:20,219 --> 00:54:22,262
buried in the frozen ground.

78
00:54:23,472 --> 00:54:25,182
Like the rest of your family.

79
00:54:27,351 --> 00:54:28,352
And you...

80
00:54:33,065 --> 00:54:36,193
you will learn in
the years to come...

81
00:54:38,737 --> 00:54:42,533
Siberia is a very bad
place to be immortal.

82
00:56:08,702 --> 00:56:09,745
That's not good.

83
00:57:25,237 --> 00:57:26,613
Step aside.

84
00:58:32,262 --> 00:58:33,514
Everything okay?

85
00:58:53,116 --> 00:58:54,117
No.

86
00:59:24,189 --> 00:59:25,357
Yeagor!

87
00:59:27,776 --> 00:59:28,777
Yeagor!

88
00:59:31,446 --> 00:59:34,199
If you give me what
I got coming to me...

89
00:59:36,326 --> 00:59:38,036
I would like to be on my way.

90
00:59:40,163 --> 00:59:42,165
You'll get what's coming to you.

91
00:59:43,292 --> 00:59:44,543
But first,

92
00:59:45,335 --> 00:59:46,712
let's celebrate.

93
00:59:51,466 --> 00:59:52,509
To Yeagor.

94
00:59:53,177 --> 00:59:54,261
Yeagor!

95
00:59:55,053 --> 00:59:56,221
Yeagor!

96
00:59:57,681 --> 01:00:00,225
Yeagor!

97
01:09:31,255 --> 01:09:32,881
This is for you.

98
01:09:44,268 --> 01:09:46,019
And this is for you.

99
01:14:15,205 --> 01:14:16,623
Was that your revenge?

100
01:14:18,876 --> 01:14:21,837
I expected something legendary.

101
01:14:47,571 --> 01:14:48,906
Look at me.

102
01:15:50,092 --> 01:15:51,885
Any last words?

103
01:15:53,178 --> 01:15:54,555
Spit it out!

104
01:21:48,325 --> 01:21:52,162
We thought you
might need some help?

105
01:22:30,117 --> 01:22:31,827
No need to say anything.

